<div type="definition">
<p>GARMENT WORN on the STOMACH AND HANGING LOOSELY on the SIDES.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general term for lower garments is cháng 裳.</p>
<p>2. Qún 裙 refers to the ankle-long skirt worn by women, but in ancient China this could also be worn by men. The term became current only in Eastern Han times.</p>
<p>3. Chān 襜 refers to an apron worn by men, usually unembroidered, and the word is rare.</p>
        </div>
